Package: bcsnsm
Type: Package
Title: Multivariate Box-Cox Symmetric Regression Models with Copula Dependence
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2024-05-05
Authors@R: person(
  "Rodrigo", "M R de Medeiros",
  email = "rodrigo.matheus@live.com",
  role = c("aut", "cre"),
  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8101-3038"))
Description: A comprehensive framework for analyzing multivariate positive continuous data based on 
    the multivariate Box-Cox symmetric regression models generated by a normal scale mixture copula
    (the so-called class of BCS-NSM regression models). Each margin can follow a different Box-Cox symmetric
    distribution, providing flexibility to accommodate data with different types of marginal distributions. The
    dependence within the BCS-NSM models is entirely described by a normal scale mixture
    copula, regardless of the marginal specifications. The package also provides tools for
    estimating and assessing goodness-of-fit in the associated class of multivariate regression
    models. This setting allows modeling d-dimensional positive continuous data as a function of
    explanatory variables.
